152 #define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
153  while (false) { \
154  *(static_cast<T* volatile*>(0)) = static_cast<S*>(0); \
155  }

188 template <class T>
189 class Local {
190  public:
191  V8_INLINE Local() : val_(nullptr) {}
192  template <class S>
193  V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
194  : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
200  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
201  }
202 
206  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
207 
211  V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = nullptr; }
212 
213  V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
214 
215  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
216 
227  template <class S>
228  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
229  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
230  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
231  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
232  if (b == nullptr) return false;
233  return *a == *b;
234  }
235 
236  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
237  const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
238  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
239  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
240  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
241  if (b == nullptr) return false;
242  return *a == *b;
243  }
244 
255  template <class S>
256  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
257  return !operator==(that);
258  }
259 
260  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
261  const Persistent<S>& that) const {
262  return !operator==(that);
263  }
264 
270  template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
271 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
272  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
273  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
274  if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
275 #endif
276  return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
277  }
278 
284  template <class S>
285  V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
286  return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
287  }
288 
294  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
295  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
296  const PersistentBase<T>& that);
297  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
298  const TracedReferenceBase<T>& that);
299 
300  private:
301  friend class Utils;
302  template<class F> friend class Eternal;
303  template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
304  template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
305  template<class F> friend class Local;
306  template <class F>
307  friend class MaybeLocal;
308  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
309  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
310  friend class String;
311  friend class Object;
312  friend class Context;
313  friend class Isolate;
314  friend class Private;
315  template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
316  friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
317  friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
318  friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
319  friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
320  friend class HandleScope;
321  friend class EscapableHandleScope;
322  template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
323  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
324  template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
325  template <class F>
326  friend class ReturnValue;
327  template <class F>

329  template <class F>
330  friend class TracedGlobal;
331  template <class F>
332  friend class TracedReferenceBase;
333  template <class F>
334  friend class TracedReference;

337  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
338  T* val_;

370 
375  template <class S>
376  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
377  out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
378  return !IsEmpty();
379  }

393  return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);

421 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
422 static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
423 
424 template <typename T>
425 class WeakCallbackInfo {
426  public:
427  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
428 
429  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
430  void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
431  Callback* callback)
432  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
433  for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
434  embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
435  }
436  }
437 
438  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
439  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
440  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
441 
442  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
443  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
444  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
445  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
446  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
447  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
448  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
449 
450  private:
451  Isolate* isolate_;
452  T* parameter_;
453  Callback* callback_;
454  void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
455 };
456 
457 
458 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
459 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
460 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
461 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
462 // possible to request a second pass callback.
463 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
464 
478 template <class T> class PersistentBase {

500  V8_INLINE void Empty() { val_ = 0; }
501 
502  V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
503  return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this);
504  }
505 
506  template <class S>

508  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
509  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
510  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;

513  }

518  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
519  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
520  if (b == nullptr) return false;
521  return *a == *b;
522  }

613 template<class T>
614 class NonCopyablePersistentTraits {
615  public:
616  typedef Persistent<T, NonCopyablePersistentTraits<T> > NonCopyablePersistent;
617  static const bool kResetInDestructor = false;
618  template<class S, class M>
619  V8_INLINE static void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
620  NonCopyablePersistent* dest) {
621  Uncompilable<Object>();
622  }
623  // TODO(dcarney): come up with a good compile error here.
624  template<class O> V8_INLINE static void Uncompilable() {
625  TYPE_CHECK(O, Primitive);
626  }
627 };

654 template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
655  public:
659  V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
665  template <class S>
666  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
667  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
668  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
669  }
675  template <class S, class M2>
676  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
677  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
678  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
679  }
686  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {
687  Copy(that);
688  }
689  template <class S, class M2>
690  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
691  Copy(that);
692  }
693  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) {
694  Copy(that);
695  return *this;
696  }
697  template <class S, class M2>
698  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
699  Copy(that);
700  return *this;
701  }
707  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
708  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
709  }
710 
711  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
712  template <class S>
713  V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
714 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
715  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
716  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
717  if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
718 #endif
719  return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
720  }
721 
722  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
723  template <class S>
724  V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
725  return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
726  }
727 
728  private:
729  friend class Isolate;
730  friend class Utils;
731  template<class F> friend class Local;
732  template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
733  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
734 
735  explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
736  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
737  template<class S, class M2>
738  V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
739 };

835 template <typename T>

857  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_);
858  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
859  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
860  if (b == nullptr) return false;
861  return *a == *b;
862  }
863 
864  template <class S>
865  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
866  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_);
867  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
868  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
869  if (b == nullptr) return false;
870  return *a == *b;
871  }
872

875  return !operator==(that);
876  }
877

897  const_cast<TracedReferenceBase<T>&>(*this));
898  }
899 
900  private:

902

907 
908  V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that, void* slot,
909  DestructionMode destruction_mode);

1057 template <typename T>

1073  template <class S>
1074  TracedReference(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that) : TracedReferenceBase<T>() {
1075  this->val_ = this->New(isolate, that.val_, &this->val_,
1076  TracedReferenceBase<T>::kWithoutDestructor);
1077  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
1078  }
1079 
1084  V8_INLINE TracedReference(TracedReference&& other) {
1085  // Forward to operator=.
1086  *this = std::move(other);
1087  }
1088 
1093  template <typename S>
1094  V8_INLINE TracedReference(TracedReference<S>&& other) {
1095  // Forward to operator=.
1096  *this = std::move(other);
1097  }
1098 
1103  V8_INLINE TracedReference(const TracedReference& other) {
1104  // Forward to operator=;
1105  *this = other;
1106  }
1107 
1112  template <typename S>
1113  V8_INLINE TracedReference(const TracedReference<S>& other) {
1114  // Forward to operator=;
1115  *this = other;
1116  }
1117 
1121  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(TracedReference&& rhs);
1122 
1126  template <class S>
1127  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(TracedReference<S>&& rhs);
1128 
1135  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference& rhs);
1136 
1143  template <class S>
1144  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference<S>& rhs);
1145 
1150  template <class S>
1151  V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
1152 
1153  template <class S>
1154  V8_INLINE TracedReference<S>& As() const {
1155  return reinterpret_cast<TracedReference<S>&>(
1156  const_cast<TracedReference<T>&>(*this));
1157  }
1158 
1169  V8_DEPRECATED("Use TracedGlobal<> if callbacks are required.")
1170  V8_INLINE void SetFinalizationCallback(
1171  void* parameter, WeakCallbackInfo<void>::Callback callback);
1172 };

1353 class ScriptOriginOptions {
1354  public:
1355  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1356  bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1357  bool is_module = false)
1358  : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1359  (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1360  (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1361  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1362  : flags_(flags &
1363  (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1364 
1365  bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1366  return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1367  }
1368  bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1369  bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1370  bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1371 
1372  int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1373 
1374  private:
1375  enum {
1376  kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1377  kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1378  kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1379  kIsModule = 1 << 3
1380  };
1381  const int flags_;
1382 };

1635 class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1636  public:
1644  struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1645  enum BufferPolicy {
1646  BufferNotOwned,
1647  BufferOwned
1648  };
1649 
1650  CachedData()
1651  : data(nullptr),
1652  length(0),
1653  rejected(false),
1654  buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1655 
1656  // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1657  // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1658  // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1659  // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1660  CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1661  BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1662  ~CachedData();
1663  // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1664  // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1665  const uint8_t* data;
1666  int length;
1667  bool rejected;
1668  BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1669 
1670  // Prevent copying.
1671  CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1672  CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1673  };

1689  // alive.
1690  V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;

1693

3661 class V8_EXPORT Object : public Value {
3662  public:
3667  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> Set(Local<Context> context,
3668  Local<Value> key, Local<Value> value);
3669 
3670  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> Set(Local<Context> context, uint32_t index,
3671  Local<Value> value);
3672 
3673  // Implements CreateDataProperty (ECMA-262, 7.3.4).
3674  //
3675  // Defines a configurable, writable, enumerable property with the given value
3676  // on the object unless the property already exists and is not configurable
3677  // or the object is not extensible.
3678  //
3679  // Returns true on success.
3680  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> CreateDataProperty(Local<Context> context,
3681  Local<Name> key,
3682  Local<Value> value);
3683  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> CreateDataProperty(Local<Context> context,
3684  uint32_t index,
3685  Local<Value> value);
3686 
3687  // Implements DefineOwnProperty.
3688  //
3689  // In general, CreateDataProperty will be faster, however, does not allow
3690  // for specifying attributes.
3691  //
3692  // Returns true on success.
3693  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> DefineOwnProperty(
3694  Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key, Local<Value> value,
3695  PropertyAttribute attributes = None);
3696 
3697  // Implements Object.DefineProperty(O, P, Attributes), see Ecma-262 19.1.2.4.
3698  //
3699  // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3700  // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3701  //
3702  // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
3703  //
3704  // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
3705  // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.
3706  //
3707  // The PropertyDescriptor can change when redefining a property.

4201 template<typename T>
4202 class ReturnValue {
4203  public:
4204  template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
4205  : value_(that.value_) {
4206  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
4207  }
4208  // Local setters
4209  template <typename S>
4210  V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
4211  template <typename S>
4212  V8_INLINE void Set(const TracedReferenceBase<S>& handle);
4213  template <typename S>
4214  V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
4215  // Fast primitive setters
4216  V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
4217  V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
4218  V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
4219  V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
4220  // Fast JS primitive setters
4221  V8_INLINE void SetNull();
4222  V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
4223  V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
4224  // Convenience getter for Isolate
4225  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
4226 
4227  // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
4228  template <typename S>
4229  V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
4230 
4231  // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
4232  // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
4233  // value.
4234  V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
4235 
4236  private:
4237  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
4238  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
4239  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
4240  template <class F, class G, class H>
4241  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
4242  V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Address value) { *value_ = value; }
4243  V8_INLINE internal::Address GetDefaultValue();
4244  V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Address* slot);
4245  internal::Address* value_;
4246 };

6932 class V8_EXPORT Extension { // NOLINT

6937  const char** deps = nullptr, int source_length = -1);
6938  virtual ~Extension() { delete source_; }

6940  Isolate* isolate, Local<String> name) {
6941  return Local<FunctionTemplate>();
6942  }
6943 
6944  const char* name() const { return name_; }
6945  size_t source_length() const { return source_length_; }
6946  const String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* source() const {
6947  return source_;
6948  }
6949  int dependency_count() const { return dep_count_; }
6950  const char** dependencies() const { return deps_; }
6951  void set_auto_enable(bool value) { auto_enable_ = value; }
6952  bool auto_enable() { return auto_enable_; }
6953 
6954  // Disallow copying and assigning.
6955  Extension(const Extension&) = delete;
6956  void operator=(const Extension&) = delete;
6957 
6958  private:
6959  const char* name_;
6960  size_t source_length_; // expected to initialize before source_
6961  String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* source_;
6962  int dep_count_;
6963  const char** deps_;
6964  bool auto_enable_;
6965 };

7668 struct JitCodeEvent {
7669  enum EventType {
7670  CODE_ADDED,
7671  CODE_MOVED,
7672  CODE_REMOVED,
7673  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
7674  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
7675  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
7676  };
7677  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
7678  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
7679  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
7680  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
7681  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
7682  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
7683 
7684  // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
7685  // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
7686  // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
7687  // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
7688  // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
7689  // function.
7690  enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
7691 
7692  // Type of event.
7693  EventType type;
7694  CodeType code_type;
7695  // Start of the instructions.
7696  void* code_start;
7697  // Size of the instructions.
7698  size_t code_len;
7699  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
7700  Local<UnboundScript> script;
7701  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
7702  // code line information which is returned from the
7703  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
7704  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
7705  void* user_data;
7706 
7707  struct name_t {
7708  // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
7709  // zero-terminated.
7710  const char* str;
7711  // Number of chars in str.
7712  size_t len;
7713  };
7714 
7715  struct line_info_t {
7716  // PC offset
7717  size_t offset;
7718  // Code position
7719  size_t pos;
7720  // The position type.
7721  PositionType position_type;
7722  };
7723 
7724  struct wasm_source_info_t {
7725  // Source file name.
7726  const char* filename;
7727  // Length of filename.
7728  size_t filename_size;
7729  // Line number table, which maps offsets of JITted code to line numbers of
7730  // source file.
7731  const line_info_t* line_number_table;
7732  // Number of entries in the line number table.
7733  size_t line_number_table_size;
7734  };
7735 
7736  wasm_source_info_t* wasm_source_info;
7737 
7738  union {
7739  // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
7740  struct name_t name;
7741 
7742  // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
7743  struct line_info_t line_info;
7744 
7745  // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
7746  void* new_code_start;
7747  };
7748 
7749  Isolate* isolate;
7750 };
7751 
7757 enum RAILMode : unsigned {
7758  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
7759  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
7760  // Throughput may be throttled.
7761  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
7762  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
7763  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
7764  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
7765  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
7766  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
7767  // in this mode.
7768  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
7769  // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
7770  // turn off latency optimizations.
7771  PERFORMANCE_LOAD
7772 };
7773 
7777 enum JitCodeEventOptions {
7778  kJitCodeEventDefault = 0,
7779  // Generate callbacks for already existent code.
7780  kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1
7781 };

8009  */
8010  v8::Isolate* isolate() const { return isolate_; }

9825 
9836 template <class T>
9837 class Maybe {
9838  public:
9839  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
9840  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
9841 
9845  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
9846 
9851  V8_INLINE void Check() const {
9852  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
9853  }
9854 
9859  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
9860  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
9861  return IsJust();
9862  }
9863 
9868  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
9869  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
9870  return value_;
9871  }
9872 
9877  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
9878  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
9879  }
9880 
9881  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
9882  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
9883  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
9884  }
9885 
9886  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
9887  return !operator==(other);
9888  }
9889 
9890  private:
9891  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
9892  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
9893 
9894  bool has_value_;
9895  T value_;
9896 
9897  template <class U>
9898  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
9899  template <class U>
9900  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
9901 };
9902 
9903 template <class T>
9904 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
9905  return Maybe<T>();
9906 }
9907 
9908 template <class T>
9909 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
9910  return Maybe<T>(t);
9911 }
9912 
9913 // A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
9914 template <>
9915 class Maybe<void> {
9916  public:
9917  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
9918  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
9919 
9920  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
9921  return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
9922  }
9923 
9924  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
9925  return !operator==(other);
9926  }
9927 
9928  private:
9929  struct JustTag {};
9930 
9931  Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
9932  explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
9933 
9934  bool is_valid_;
9935 
9936  template <class U>
9937  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
9938  friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
9939 };
9940 
9941 inline Maybe<void> JustVoid() { return Maybe<void>(Maybe<void>::JustTag()); }

10678  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10679  this->Reset();
10680  if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
10681  internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
10682  this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyGlobalReference(p));
10683  M::Copy(that, this);
10684 }

10771 template <class T>

10774  V8::MoveGlobalReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&other.val_),
10775  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));

10777  }

10780 template <class T>
10781 template <class S>
10782 Global<T>& Global<T>::operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) {
10783  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
10784  if (this != &rhs) {
10785  this->Reset();
10786  if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
10787  this->val_ = rhs.val_;
10788  V8::MoveGlobalReference(
10789  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&rhs.val_),
10790  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
10791  rhs.val_ = nullptr;
10792  }
10793  }
10794  return *this;
10795 }

10988 template<typename T>
10989 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
10990  TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
10991  typedef internal::Internals I;
10992  if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
10993  *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
10994  return;
10995  }
10996  Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
10997 }
10998 
10999 template<typename T>
11000 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
11001  TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
11002  // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
11003  bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
11004  if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
11005  Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
11006  return;
11007  }
11008  Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
11009 }
11010 
11011 template<typename T>
11012 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
11013  TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
11014  typedef internal::Internals I;
11015  int root_index;
11016  if (value) {
11017  root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
11018  } else {
11019  root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
11020  }
11021  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
11022 }
11023 
11024 template<typename T>
11025 void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {
11026  TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
11027  typedef internal::Internals I;
11028  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
11029 }
11030 
11031 template<typename T>
11032 void ReturnValue<T>::SetUndefined() {
11033  TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
11034  typedef internal::Internals I;
11035  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
11036 }
11037 
11038 template<typename T>
11039 void ReturnValue<T>::SetEmptyString() {
11040  TYPE_CHECK(T, String);
11041  typedef internal::Internals I;
11042  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
11043 }
11044 
11045 template <typename T>
11046 Isolate* ReturnValue<T>::GetIsolate() const {
11047  // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
11048  return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
11049 }
11050 
11051 template <typename T>
11052 Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
11053  typedef internal::Internals I;
11054  if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
11055  return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
11056  return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
11057 }
11058 
11059 template <typename T>
11060 template <typename S>
11061 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(S* whatever) {
11062  // Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
11063  TYPE_CHECK(S*, Primitive);
11064 }
11065 
11066 template <typename T>
11067 internal::Address ReturnValue<T>::GetDefaultValue() {
11068  // Default value is always the pointer below value_ on the stack.
11069  return value_[-1];
11070 }

11072 template <typename T>

11078 template<typename T>
11079 Local<Value> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::operator[](int i) const {
11080  if (i < 0 || length_ <= i) return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
11081  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(values_ - i));
11082 }

11241 
11242 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
11243 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11244  typedef internal::Address A;
11245  typedef internal::Internals I;
11246  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11247  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11248  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11249  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11250  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11251  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11252  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
11253  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11254  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(obj, offset);
11255 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11256  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11257  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11258  value = I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(obj, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11259 #endif
11260  internal::Isolate* isolate =
11261  internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj);
11262  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11263  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11264  }
11265 #endif
11266  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
11267 }
11268 
11269 
11270 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
11271 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11272  typedef internal::Address A;
11273  typedef internal::Internals I;
11274  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11275  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11276  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11277  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11278  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11279  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11280  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
11281  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11282  return I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, offset);
11283  }
11284 #endif
11285  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
11286 }

11296 Local<String> String::Empty(Isolate* isolate) {
11297  typedef internal::Address S;
11298  typedef internal::Internals I;
11299  I::CheckInitialized(isolate);
11300  S* slot = I::GetRoot(isolate, I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
11301  return Local<String>(reinterpret_cast<String*>(slot));
11302 }

11304 
11305 String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
11306  typedef internal::Address A;
11307  typedef internal::Internals I;
11308  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11309 
11310  ExternalStringResource* result;
11311  if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
11312  void* value = I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
11313  result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
11314  } else {
11315  result = GetExternalStringResourceSlow();
11316  }
11317 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11318  VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
11319 #endif
11320  return result;
11321 }
11322 
11323 
11324 String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
11325  String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
11326  typedef internal::Address A;
11327  typedef internal::Internals I;
11328  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11329  int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
11330  *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
11331  ExternalStringResourceBase* resource;
11332  if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
11333  type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
11334  void* value = I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
11335  resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
11336  } else {
11337  resource = GetExternalStringResourceBaseSlow(encoding_out);
11338  }
11339 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11340  VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
11341 #endif
11342  return resource;
11343 }

11351 #endif

11353 
11354 bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
11355  typedef internal::Address A;
11356  typedef internal::Internals I;
11357  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11358  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11359  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11360  return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
11361 }

11372 bool Value::QuickIsNull() const {
11373  typedef internal::Address A;
11374  typedef internal::Internals I;
11375  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11376  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11377  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11378  return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kNullOddballKind);
11379 }

11381 bool Value::IsNullOrUndefined() const {
11382 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11383  return FullIsNull() || FullIsUndefined();
11384 #else
11385  return QuickIsNullOrUndefined();
11386 #endif
11387 }
11388 
11389 bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
11390  typedef internal::Address A;
11391  typedef internal::Internals I;
11392  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11393  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11394  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11395  int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
11396  return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
11397 }

11777 template <typename T>
11778 bool PropertyCallbackInfo<T>::ShouldThrowOnError() const {
11779  typedef internal::Internals I;
11780  if (args_[kShouldThrowOnErrorIndex] !=
11781  I::IntToSmi(I::kInferShouldThrowMode)) {
11782  return args_[kShouldThrowOnErrorIndex] != I::IntToSmi(I::kDontThrow);
11783  }
11784  return v8::internal::ShouldThrowOnError(
11785  reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Isolate*>(GetIsolate()));
11786 }

11847 
11848 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
11849  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
11850  typedef internal::Internals I;
11851  constexpr int64_t kMemoryReducerActivationLimit = 32 * 1024 * 1024;
11852  int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
11853  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
11854  int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
11855  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
11856  int64_t* external_memory_at_last_mc =
11857  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
11858  I::kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset);
11859 
11860  // Embedders are weird: we see both over- and underflows here. Perform the
11861  // addition with unsigned types to avoid undefined behavior.
11862  const int64_t amount =
11863  static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(change_in_bytes) +
11864  static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory));
11865  *external_memory = amount;
11866 
11867  int64_t allocation_diff_since_last_mc =
11868  static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory) -
11869  static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory_at_last_mc));
11870  // Only check memory pressure and potentially trigger GC if the amount of
11871  // external memory increased.
11872  if (allocation_diff_since_last_mc > kMemoryReducerActivationLimit) {
11873  CheckMemoryPressure();
11874  }
11875 
11876  if (change_in_bytes < 0) {
11877  const int64_t lower_limit =
11878  static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory_limit) +
11879  static_cast<uint64_t>(change_in_bytes));
11880  if (lower_limit > I::kExternalAllocationSoftLimit) {
11881  *external_memory_limit = lower_limit;
11882  }
11883  } else if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > *external_memory_limit) {
11884  ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
11885  }
11886  return *external_memory;
11887 }
11888 
11889 Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
11890 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11891  typedef internal::Address A;
11892  typedef internal::Internals I;
11893  A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11894  A embedder_data =
11895  I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
11896  int value_offset =
11897  I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11898  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(embedder_data, value_offset);
11899 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11900  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11901  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11902  value =
11903  I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(embedder_data, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11904 #endif
11905  internal::Isolate* isolate = internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(
11906  *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this));
11907  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11908  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11909 #else
11910  return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
11911 #endif
11912 }
11913 
11914 
11915 void* Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(int index) {
11916 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11917  typedef internal::Address A;
11918  typedef internal::Internals I;
11919  A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11920  A embedder_data =
11921  I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
11922  int value_offset =
11923  I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11924  return I::ReadRawField<void*>(embedder_data, value_offset);
11925 #else
11926  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index);
11927 #endif
11928 }
